
**********************************  Install MiniKube & Kubectl using chocolatey package  *******************************************

1. Install kubectl cli:  choco install kubernetes-cli

2. Install Minikube: choco install minikube

3. Check Minikuber version installed on machine: minikube version

4. Check available version of Kubernetes: minikube get-k8s-versions

5. Update Minikube: minikube update-check

6. Run Minikube: minikube start

7. Start Minikube and suggest to use virtual box specifically: minikube start --vm-driver=virtualbox

So for the first time, Minikube will download needed ISO images and start the Minikube virtual machine.To check the status of Minikube 
minikube status can be executed. If Minikube works fine the output of the command will be like below.

minikube: Running
cluster: Running
kubectl: Correctly Configured: pointing to minikube-vm at 192.168.99.100

